{
  "texts": [
    "Both thermal and depth maps provide clear contour information and a coarse pixel-wise target segmentation map.",
    "With such information, the target shape can be effectively estimated [52].",
    "[49], the number of scales is adaptively changed to fit the scale variation.",
    "SEOH [52] uses space continuity-of-depth information to achieve accurate scale estimation with negligible time cost.",
    "The pixels belonging to the target are clustered by applying the K-means method to the depth map, and the sizes of the target and search regions are determined by the clustering result."
  ]
}